      "writtenOn": "2026-06-08T15:34:36Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Good point. The idea is not to change how the interface works, but to keep Logging.Entry as one common place for all events, and use the property only to classify them.\nIf we split into multiple interfaces, clients would need to handle multiple event types separately as new ones are added. Keeping one interface keeps things simple and stable.\n’m not completely against moving to a separate interface if that’s considered a cleaner approach .  @Ptarick @Matt please add your thoughts here.",
      "parentUuid": "1b761912_496c9414",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 113,
        "startChar": 9,
        "endLine": 114,
        "endChar": 33
      },
      "revId": "88c111f7cf7c378832050ee5dff009dc898e678e",
